    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Corn_Bt11_x_MIR162_x_NK6Ø3 -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Corn_Bt11_x_MIR162_x_NK6Ø3">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#crop_variety"/>
        <hasDesign rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#decrease_binding_afinity_for_glyphosate"/>
        <hasDesign rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#eliminate_herbicidal_activity_of_glufosinate"/>
        <hasDesign rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#produce_enzyme_to_metabolise_mannose"/>
        <hasDesign rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#toxic_to_insect"/>
        <hasSpecies rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Agrobacterium_tumefaciens"/>
        <hasSpecies rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Bacillus_thuringiensis"/>
        <hasSpecies rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Escherichia_coli"/>
        <hasSpecies rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Streptomyces_viridochromogenes"/>
        <hasSpecies rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#corn"/>
        <authorisation_country>Argentina</authorisation_country>
        <authorisation_country>Brazil</authorisation_country>
        <authorisation_country>Paraguay</authorisation_country>
        <developed_by>Syngenta</developed_by>
        <has_name>Agrisure® Viptera™ 2100 Roundup Ready™ 2 Maize</has_name>
        <resistance_to_insect>Lepidoptera</resistance_to_insect>
        <tolerance_to_herbicide>glufosinate</tolerance_to_herbicide>
        <tolerance_to_herbicide>glyphosate</tolerance_to_herbicide>
        <rdfs:comment>Corn variety that has developed by combining three individual transformation events using classical genetic improvement. This variety has the ability to eliminate glufosinate herbicidal activity by the introduction of pat transgene derived from Streptomyces viridochromogenes; to create toxin to lepidopteran insects by the introduction of cry1Ab transgene derived from Bacillus thuringiensis subsp. kumamotoensis and vip3Aa20 transgene derived from Bacillus thuringiensis strain AB88; to decrease glyphosate herbicides binding affinity by the introduction of cp2 epsps derived from 	Agrobacterium tumefaciens strain CP4; and to metabolize mannose by the introduction of pmi transgene derived from Eschericia coli</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>https://www.isaaa.org/gmapprovaldatabase/event/default.asp?EventID=594&amp;Event=Bt11%20x%20MIR162%20x%20NK6%C3%983
https://www.fao.org/food/food-safety-quality/gm-foods-platform/browse-information-by/oecd-unique-identifier/oecd-unique-identifier-details/en/?ui=1637296</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


