    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Muscadine_seedless -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#Muscadine_seedless">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#crop_variety"/>
        <hasDesign rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#suppressing_the_seedlessness_gene"/>
        <hasSpecies rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/90958855/ontologies/2024/8/riesma_thesis#muscadine"/>
        <developed_by>Florida A&amp;M University</developed_by>
        <rdfs:comment>Muscadine grape variety that has no seed because its VroAGL11 gene knocked out by using CRISPR-cas9 gene editing technology. The CRISPR-cas9 constructs or ribonucleoproteins (RNPs) are delivered to grape calli/protoplasts via Agrobacterium-mediated plasmids and/or directly (protoplast transfection) to knockout/knockdown the muscadine VroAGL11 gene.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>https://portal.nifa.usda.gov/web/crisprojectpages/1026062-establishing-gene-editing-technology-to-develop-seedless-muscadine-table-grape.html</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


