        <resistance_to_disease>potato leaf roll virus (PLRV) disease</resistance_to_disease>
        <resistance_to_insect>Coleopteran</resistance_to_insect>
        <rdfs:comment>Potato variety that has ability to create toxin to coleopteran insect from the over expression of cry3A gene derived from Bacillus thuringiensis subsp. tenebrionis, metabolise seomycin and kanamycing antibiotic from marker selected nptll gene from Escherichia coli Tn5 transposon, and produce viral replication gene that leads to plrv orf1/0rf2 gene silencing</rdfs:comment>
